President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum. Beijing, December 11 (Xinhua) - On December 11, President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum. President Xi pointed out that the world is experiencing a major change of unprecedented magnitude in a hundred years, with global technological innovation entering a period of intensive activity, and the new round of technological revolution and industrial transformation is having a profound impact on the global economic structure. The Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area should focus on building a strategy of international scientific and technological innovation center and strive to build a global scientific and technological innovation highland, promoting the development of emerging industries. China is willing to work with scientists and international scientific and technological organizations from all over the world to closely cooperate in international scientific and technological exchange, strengthen research on major scientific issues, promote the cracking of common scientific and technological problems, deepen collaboration on key scientific projects, and jointly promote the development of the world's science cause and better benefit humanity. The 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum opened on the same day in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province, with the theme "Exploring the Future, Sharing Science". It was hosted by the People's Government of Guangdong Province.
